  "page": "Silver Denys",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For other characters with the same name, see <a href=\"/index.php/Denys\" title=\"Denys\">Denys</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Silver Denys</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Silver_denys_cannibal.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Silver denys cannibal.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ed/Silver_denys_cannibal.png/300px-Silver_denys_cannibal.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"473\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ed/Silver_denys_cannibal.png/450px-Silver_denys_cannibal.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ed/Silver_denys_cannibal.png/600px-Silver_denys_cannibal.png 2x\" /></a><div>The Cannibal descends upon Silver Denys and his sons by Lucian Tumani ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Race</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Valyrians\" title=\"Valyrians\">Valyrian</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\nSons<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\nRobert Rhodes</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">Season 2</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Silver Denys</b> was a man living on <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> at the outset of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>, Denys is portrayed by Robert Rhodes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Silver_Denys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Silver Denys claimed to be descended from a <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> son of King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While none denied that Silver Denys had <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian\" title=\"Valyrian\">Valyrian</a> blood due to his silver hair and <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_eyes\" title=\"Purple eyes\">purple eyes</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> his claim of being a descendant of Maegor is called into doubt as the king was infamously unable to produce a living heir, despite marrying multiple fertile women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> It is possible that Denys's bloodline come from a different Valyrian.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Silver_Denys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>When Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sowing\" title=\"Sowing\">called</a> for dragonriders, Denys had his arm ripped off in his attempt to mount <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a>. While his sons were trying to staunch the wound, <a href=\"/index.php/Cannibal_(dragon)\" title=\"Cannibal (dragon)\">the Cannibal</a> descended on them and devoured Denys along with his sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theories\">Theories</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Silver_Denys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Theories\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It is possible that Denys is a descendant of the red-headed <a href=\"/index.php/Man-at-arms\" title=\"Man-at-arms\">man-at-arms</a> who declared to be <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor the Cruel</a>'s natural son during the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Council_of_101_AC\" title=\"Great Council of 101 AC\">Great Council of 101 AC</a>. However, it seems that the two characters are unrelated, since their hair colors don't match, the man-at arms is not introduced as a potential <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonseeds\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragonseeds\">seed</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>, and in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> Denys asserted to be himself a bastard son of Maegor, a claim later fixed in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Silver_Denys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">In <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i>, Silver Denys claims \"to be a bastard son of King Maegor the Cruel\". This was later changed into \"to be descended from a bastard son of Maegor the Cruel\" in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>. <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> most likely made this change to better fit the timeline as Maegor died eighty-one years before the Dance.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Silver_Denys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - The Red Dragon and the Gold.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Redanian Intelligence: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://redanianintelligence.com/2023/08/13/house-of-the-dragon-season-2-adds-silver-denys-dragonseed/\">Silver Denys Cast (August 13, 2023)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Maegor I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Heirs of the Dragon - A Question of Succession.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403143528\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.086 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.281 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1038/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10861/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 9283/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 2533/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4295/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.180/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.87 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  267.981      1 -total\n 86.61%  232.103      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 86.11%  230.762      1 Template:Infobox\n 10.75%   28.811     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  9.58%   25.